Product.Product_Description: Copper L-Aspartate 1% is the synthesized product of L-Aspartic Acid and Cupric Carbonate with a generous portion of Mannitol added to the mixture to keep the level of Copper at 1%. Copper and L-Aspartic Acid are both naturally occurring in the body, making them very bioavailable, while Mannitol is present merely as a carrier. Whey is a substance produced during cheese production. It is the liquid content that remains after the milk has curdled and coagulated. It contains lactalbumin and 5% lactose that has been diluted in water. Whey can be processed and isolated into three different types of protein: Whey Protein Isolate, Whey Protein Concentrate and Whey Protein Hydrolysate. Whey Protein Isolate is the purest form, where the water, fats and lactose content have been removed. It contains a larger amount of pure protein than Whey Protein Concentrate and Whey Protein Hydrolysate.

Mannitol is a white, crystalline sugar alcohol that is used as sugar substitute. Mannitol is a polyol (sugar alcohol) widely used in the food and pharmaceutical industries due to its unique functional properties. It is about half as sweet as table sugar (sucrose) and has a desirable cooling effect often used to mask bitter taste, making it a popular low-calorie sweetener for cooking.

Citric Acid is a naturally occurring acid found primarily in several varieties of fruits and vegetables, with citrus fruits such as lemons and limes containing the highest amounts. This organic acid is frequently used as a food additive, preservative, cosmetic ingredient and powerful cleaning agent. Citric acid can be purchased as a white crystalline powder.
